name: 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: Also oxidizes S-3-hydroxyacyl-N-acylthioethanolamine and S-3-hydroxyacyl-hydrolipoate. Some enzymes act, more slowly, with NADP+. Broad specificity to acyl chain-length (cf. EC 1.1.1.211 [long-chain-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase]).

orthologs.K01825: 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase / enoyl-CoA hydratase / 3-hydroxybutyryl-CoA epimerase / enoyl-CoA isomerase

references.title: Solubilization and partial characterisation of particulate dehydrogenases from Clostridium kluyveri.
The enzymic oxidation of alpha- and 2-beta-hydroxybutyrate.
Crystalline beta-hydroxybutyryl dehydrogenase from pig heart.
Studies on the fatty acid oxidizing system of animal tissues. VI. beta-Hydroxyacyl coenzyme A dehydrogenase.
